org.apache.hadoop.hbase

Interface ShareableMemory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CellUtil.ShareableMemoryTagRewriteCell, KeyValueCodec.ByteBufferedKeyValueDecoder.ShareableMemoryKeyValue, KeyValueCodec.ByteBufferedKeyValueDecoder.ShareableMemoryNoTagsKeyValue

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
public interface ShareableMemory
    A cell implementing this interface would mean that the memory area backing this cell will refer to a memory area that could be part of a larger common memory area used by the RegionServer. This might be the bigger memory chunk where the RPC requests are read into. If an exclusive instance is required, use the cloneToCell() to have the contents of the cell copied to an exclusive memory area.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Cell cloneToCell()
      Does a deep copy of the contents to a new memory area and returns it in the form of a cell.
